* Now, we use [usort()](https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.usort.php) to compare the 2 subarrays via `name` through [strcmp()](https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.strcmp.php) and return the result.

* We again iterate through them and use [array_keys()](https://www.php.net/manual/en/function.array-keys.php) to iterate over the data set. We do this as we are going to restore the parent key back without running into concurrent modification issue while iterating over the same array. 

